    <h3><a href="/2012-12-14/PageKite_for_Android_updated">PageKite for Android updated</a></h3>
    
    <span class="img"><img class=gravatar src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2faf289f4fe770b25610ce9622789eca/?default=&amp;amp;s=40" height="40" width="40"/></span>
    
    <p class="meta">
      <span class="by">By Bjarni Rúnar</span>
      <span class="timestamp">Dec. 14, 2012, 4:24 p.m.</span>
    </p>
    <div class="content">
  
      <p>We just pushed version 1.007 of the <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.pagekite.app">PageKite Android App</a> to Google Play.</p>
<p>Highlights:</p>
<ul>
<li>Experimental compatibility with legacy Android 1.6 devices.</li>
<li>Fixed a memory leak which could cause the app (or even the phone) to crash</li>
<li>Fixed a problem where fast uploads could cause kites to disconnect</li>
</ul>
<p>Upgrading is recommended, but note that it may take a little while for the Play store to list the new version.  People who have the app installed should be notified automatically when it becomes available.</p>
  
    </div>

