  <li>
    <h3><a href="/2012-12-04/Pagekite_py_0_5_4a_released">Pagekite.py 0.5.4a released</a></h3>
    
    <p class="meta">
      
      <span class="timestamp">Dec. 4, 2012, 6:58 p.m.</span>
    </p>
    <div class="content">
  
      <p>Last Friday we released <code>pagekite.py</code> version 0.5.4a.  These are the changes and bugfixes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Improved --proxy argument handling to do chains properly</li>
<li>Added --client_acl and --tunnel_acl</li>
<li>Fixed bug in --pemfile</li>
<li>Fixed built-in HTTPS server's silly incompatibility with SNI.</li>
<li>Added --selfsign for easily enabling self-signed HTTPS.</li>
<li>Fixed behavior of --remove and --disable for nonexistant kites.</li>
</ul>
<p>This release also comes with two new how-to pages on the wiki:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Howto/ShareFilesSecurely/">Sharing Files and Folders Securely</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Howto/TlsClientAuthentication/">Using TLS client authentication with PageKite</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The first is how-to is potentially useful for everyone, the second really only applies to folks who are running their own front-end relay servers.  Enjoy!</p>
  
    </div>

